      <tr>
        <td height="20" align="left" valign="top" class="textalign"><p>E-tickets  <br /> <br />
          All tickets sold on  The UK Flights are electronic tickets. Once you've made your booking, it's  stored electronically in the airline reservation system. The UK Flights will  send you a confirmation email with your booking reference number and E-ticket  number, which serves as a receipt for your e-ticket. You will&nbsp;<strong>NOT</strong>&nbsp;receive a physical 'e-ticket' or paper  tickets to present at the airport. We recommend that you take a printout of  your confirmation email with you, although many airlines won't ask to see this.  During the booking process, you will be given  the choice of e-ticket or paper ticket.&nbsp;Please  note that airlines have their own rules and regulations with regard to  e-ticketing. The UK Flights cannot be held responsible for non-compliance with  these rules and regulations and strongly recommends that you check these  details with your airline in advance of travel. <br /><br />
          Ticket Delivery<strong> </strong><br /><br />
          The UK  Flights on the information that you provide as  being accurate and therefore cannot be held responsible if your paper tickets  are lost due to an incorrect address or your e-ticket does not arrive due to an  incorrect email address or your junk email settings. You must notify us  immediately if you change your email address or contact telephone number. In  addition, please check that the name on your passport matches the name on your  ticket and/or booking confirmation. Please note that <strong>The UK Flights</strong> does  not deliver paper tickets outside the UK. Also, if you have any special  delivery requirements (such as flats with security gates) then you should  advise us of this immediately after booking. It is your responsibility to  advise us if you have not received your tickets. If you hold any other booking,  either with The UK Flights or another  agent, then it is your responsibility to advise us that you need tickets from  us by a certain time. The UK Flights would  recommend that you do this before completing the booking. This will help us  decide if express delivery is required.&nbsp;</p></td>
